wiki.content: Jamie Cullum is a British pop and jazz-pop singer, songwriter, pianist, guitarist and drummer, born in 20 August 1979 in Essex. Awards : in the British Jazz Awards - the "Rising Star" award in 2003, BRIT Awards - nominated in the "British Breakthrough Act" category in 2004, in the BRIT Awards - nominated for "Best Male Artist" and "Best Live Act" in 2005, BBC Jazz Awards - "Artist Of The Year", Ronnie Scotts Jazz Award for "Best British Male" in 2007. Albums : Heard It All Before (1999), Pointless Nostalgic (2002), Twentysomething (2003), Catching Tales (2005), Live at Ronnie Scott's (2006), In the Mind of Jamie Cullum. He wrote the song "OH God" after tsunami. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.
